The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The state cabinet on Tuesday deferred the decision to revise police tax on establishments in the city and asked the home department to review the tax slabs in each category. The proposal involves revision of taxes on establishments ranging from five-star hotels to cigarette shops. According to officials, the cabinet wants the tax rates to be decided keeping in mind the volume of business of the establishments. 

 Two-and-a-half-year-old Ritu Maity was run over by a private bus near the Shyambazar five-point crossing on Tuesday morning. She was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where she died. The driver and conductor of the bus were taken into custody. 

 Police have decided to lodge a case against the organisation that had taken out a rally in the city on Monday afternoon, throwing traffic out of gear. Three complaints have been registered against the group at Entally, North Port and Maidan police stations for refusing to abide by the police directive to the members not to organise the procession.

 The economic offences wing of the Criminal Investigation Department arrested Pradip Mondal at Alipore on Tuesday for allegedly withdrawing money from the accounts of more than 50 people in a nationalised bank branch at Budge Budge.

 Governor Gopal Krishna Gandhi on Tuesday launched the book, Cornelia Sorabhji, India?s Pioneering Woman Lawyer: A Biography, by Suparna Gooptu, at Raj Bhavan. 

